wikipedia_page.main: Vincent Tinley (26 January 1828 – 19 November 1899) was an English first-class cricketer active 1851–64 who played for Nottinghamshire and Manchester as a wicketkeeper. He was born in Southwell; died in Nottingham.

response: *Francis Tinley (1819–1889), first-class cricketer with Nottinghamshire, was born here, as was his first-class cricketing brother Vincent Tinley (1828–1899).
